Sec. 13.258. DUTIES OF THE DEPARTMENT. The department shall
supervise public weighers and shall adopt rules necessary to enforce
this subchapter. On application by an interested party, the
department shall review the weight or measure of a commodity
certified by a public weigher and may require the commodity to be
reweighed or remeasured.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1041, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 2593, ch. 693, Sec. 14, eff.
Sept. 1, 1981.

